Usage: write_generalized_feedthru_paths [-help]
                                        [-dont_generalize_reverse_paths]
                                        [-dont_generalize_sub_paths]
                                        [-topological_out_file <string>]
                                        -use_topological_file <string>

-help                                   # Prints out the command usage
-dont_generalize_reverse_paths          # Generalization algorithm not to
                                        # generalize reverse chain paths
                                        # (bool, optional)
-dont_generalize_sub_paths              # Generalization algorithm not to
                                        # generalize sub-paths (bool, optional)
-topological_out_file <string>          # output topo 2.0 filename. Default:
                                        # path.topo (string, optional)
-use_topological_file <string>          # user feedthrough path guidance file
                                        # (string, required)